eventName: LIVE IMPULS with Headcornerstone and Sista Sherin
lineupRaw:
Headcornerstone
Sista Sherin
Dandelion

Following the release of their last album, „Walk On, “ in 2021, the eleven-member reggae band Headcornerstone is now playing occasional live shows again, almost with its original lineup.
The band was an integral part of Germany‘s flourishing reggae scene in the early to mid-2000s. With their albums „Cornerstone“ (2003) and „Stand Strong“ (2005), the band attracted attention far beyond Germany‘s borders in the following years. Now they‘re back, presenting earlier and current songs from their repertoire.

Sista Sherin is a singer and songwriter, based in Freiburg (Germany). She found her love and passion in Roots Reggae and Dub Music and entered the soundsystem scene as a singer in 2009. Since then she is supporting various sounds like Jah Vibes, and Siren Sisters. Her songs carry a spiritual message and are livicated to the RastafarI Movement.

The good vibes generator Dandelion Soundsystem belongs to the top of German Soundsystem culture. Over the past 24 years, they have played hundreds of performances touring Germany and a large part of Europe, setting impulses for many of today‘s Soundsystems. Hailing from Freising near Munich Dandelion plays upon their home-made, heavyweight, self-planned and self-constructed soundsystem coming with upfull edutainment and tons of good vibes. Dandelion Soundsystem is internationally notorious for its combination of extra-deep 21-inch sub-basses and sonic brilliance.

Under 18 years, entry until 23.59 for 10 Euro.
